@startuml
actor User
participant "CouponPage" as CouponPage
database DB_Beanstalkd
boundary UserMail

User ->> CouponPage : Load merchant page with cashback\n(CouponCode)
activate CouponPage
deactivate CouponPage
return Return page with discounts

note right of User #lightgreen:green;line:red;text:black;shadow:false;\n#108246;fontSize=9px:\nThe user sees all available\ndiscounts for this Merchant.\nHe can click on any discount to get more info about it,\nor he clicks directly on CashBack offer.


User ->> CouponPage : Clicks on cashback \non couponpage.com/merchantname/cashback.html?couponcode=CASHBACKCODE&uid=UserUniqueID 
activate CouponPage
deactivate CouponPage
return Returns 2 tabs, <b><u>\non tab 1</u></b>: The reLink to merchant website in new Tab(3)\n<b><i>(with uid)</i></b>, so we know where did the order come from.<b><font color=#FF5733 size="12">[Tab_1]</font></b>\n<u><b>on tab 2:</b></u>A popup window opens up asking him his email address,<br/>so that later if there are problems or questions<br/><b><font color="#ff0000"><size="+2">(we have an unique identifier - UID).</size></font></b>.<b><font color=#FDFEFE>[TAB_2] </font></b> 

group Fill Email & Submit Form [tab-2]    
    note over User,CouponPage:#pink;line:dashed;text:white;backgroundcolor=pink;borderColor=black;;fontSize = 10pt:The form contains fields like name,surname,email etc.. It also has submit button which sends data via POST method back server side script called savecashrequest.php . This will store information into our MySQL Database table named 'CashRequests'. After successful submission another AJAX request made by JavaScript function sendNewContentForCheckoutPopup() starts running asynchronously without blocking main thread execution flow anymore! Now let's see what happens next...  
end group    

